{"title_page": "American Dharma", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = American Dharma\n| image          = American Dharma poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Errol Morris]]\n| producer       = Errol Morris<br>Steven Hathaway<br>Marie Savare<br>P.J. van Sandwijk<br>Robert Fernandez\n| writer         = \n| starring       = [[Steve Bannon]]<br>[[Errol Morris]]\n| music          = [[Paul Leonard-Morgan]]\n| cinematography = Igor Martinovic\n| editing        = Steven Hathaway\n| studio         = Fourth Floor Productions<br>Maje Productions<br>Storyteller Productions<br>Moxie Pictures\n| distributor    = Utopia\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|11|1|}}\n| runtime        = 95 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/american-dharma-review-1139830 |title='American Dharma' Review |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2018-09-05 |accessdate=2019-10-31}}</ref>\n| country        = United States <br> United Kingdom\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = $51,891<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2459861505/weekend/|title=American Dharma|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=January 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/American-Dharma-(Documentary)#tab=summary|title=American Dharma|website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]]|accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''American Dharma''''' is a 2018 British-American [[documentary film]] directed by [[Errol Morris]]. The film follows the career of political strategist [[Steve Bannon]]. The film was released on November 1, 2019, by Utopia.\n\n==Release==\n''American Dharma'' premiered at the [[75th Venice International Film Festival]] on September 4th 2018<ref>{{Cite web|title=Errol Morris Tackles Steve Bannon in New Doc: \"It's Kind of a Horror Movie\"|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/errol-morris-tackles-steve-bannon-doc-kind-a-horror-movie-1136253|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref> in the \"out of competition\" category<ref>{{Cite web|title='American Dharma': Film Review {{!}} Venice 2018|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/american-dharma-review-1139830|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. [[Steve Bannon]] was not present at the premier event in Venice<ref>{{Cite news|last=Goldmann|first=A. J.|date=2018-09-05|title=Steve Bannon Documentary Debuts. Controversy Naturally Follows.|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/05/movies/steve-bannon-venice-american-dharma.html|access-date=2020-05-02|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>. The film premiered in [[Canada]] at the [[2018 Toronto International Film Festival]] (TIFF) on September 9th<ref>{{Cite web|title=Eight films about old white men playing at TIFF 2018|url=https://nowtoronto.com/api/content/8932332e-abac-11e8-858c-120e7ad5cf50/|last=Ritchie|first=Kevin|date=2018-08-29|website=NOW Magazine|language=en-us|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. The [[United States]] premiere occurred on September 29th 2018 at the [[New York Film Festival]] (NYFF)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Spotlight on Documentary {{!}} New York Film Festival|url=https://www.filmlinc.org/nyff2018/sections/spotlight-on-documentary/|website=Film at Lincoln Center|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. ''American Dharma'' was subsequently screened alongside a talk given by [[Errol Morris]] at the [[International Documentary Film Festival Amsterdam]] (IDFA) on November 18th<ref>{{Cite web|title=IDFA Program Guide 2018|url=https://issuu.com/idfa/docs/idfa_program_guide_2018|website=Issuu|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>.\n\nIn August of 2019, the film was purchased by the distribution company Utopia and slated for a theatrical release on November 1st at the [[Film Forum]] in [[New York City|New York]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Utopia nabs distribution rights for Errol Morris\u2019 \u201cAmerican Dharma\u201d|url=https://realscreen.com/2019/08/07/utopia-nabs-distribution-rights-for-errol-morris-american-dharma/|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. The trailer for theatrical release was premiered with outlet [[IndieWire]] on September 19th<ref>{{Cite web|title=\u2018American Dharma\u2019 Trailer: Steve Bannon Spars With Errol Morris in Riveting Showdown \u2014 Exclusive|url=https://www.indiewire.com/video/american-dharma-trailer-errol-morris-steve-bannon-1202174661/|last=Kohn|first=Eric|date=2019-09-19|website=IndieWire|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. The [[Film Forum]] release weekend resulted in a reported $7,522 in revenue<ref>{{Cite web|title=Box Office: \u2018Terminator: Dark Fate\u2019 Fizzles With $29 Million Debut|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/box-office/box-office-terminator-dark-fate-opening-weekend-misfire-1203391110/|last=Rubin|first=Rebecca|last2=Rubin|first2=Rebecca|date=2019-11-03|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. After 10 weeks of release, ''American Dharma'' had a box-office revenue of $50,250<ref>{{Cite web|title=Weekend Box Office Key Insights: Rise of Skywalker Threepeats as 2020 Beats 2019's First Frame|url=https://www.boxofficepro.com/weekend-box-office-key-insights-rise-of-skywalker-threepeats-as-2020-beats-2019s-first-frame/|date=2020-01-06|website=Boxoffice|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref> and ended it's run with a total revenue of 51,891<ref>{{Cite web|title=American Dharma (2019) - Financial Information|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/American-Dharma-(Documentary)|website=The Numbers|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. On January 31st the film was made available for streaming on [[Kanopy]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=New to Stream: Kanopy's Valentine's Day Recommendations!|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1122141-new-to-stream-kanopys-february-lineup-valentines-day-recommendations|last=ghermanns|date=2020-02-11|website=ComingSoon.net|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>. Since then, ''American Dharma'' has been made available on [[Apple TV]], [[Amazon Video|Amazon video]], [[Google Play]], [[Vudu]], [[Fandango (company)|Fandango]], [[Microsoft Store (digital)|Microsoft Store]], Vibuquity, [[DirecTV]], In Demand, [[Xfinity]], and [[Gracenote]]<ref>{{Citation|title=American Dharma {{!}} Utopia|url=https://www.americandharmafilm.com/watch-at-home/|language=en|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref>.\n\n==Reception==\nThe [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] gives the film an approval rating of 62%, based on 50 reviews. The website's consensus reads, \"''American Dharma'' offers a fascinating glimpse of a political influencer's public persona - and a frustrating missed opportunity to interrogate his actions and stated beliefs.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/american_dharma |title=American Dharma (2019) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |date= |accessdate=2020-02-11}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a score of 62 out of 100, based on 22 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/american-dharma |title=American Dharma Reviews |publisher=Metacritic |date= |accessdate=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* ''[[Hating Breitbart]]'' (2012), a documentary by [[Andrew Marcus]] about [[Andrew Breitbart]].\n* ''[[Fahrenheit 11/9]]'' (2018), a documentary by [[Michael Moore|Micheal Moore]] about [[Donald Trump]]'s 2016 presidential campaign and presidency.\n* ''[[The Brink (2019 film)|The Brink]]'' (2019), a documentary by [[Alison Klayman]] about [[Steve Bannon]]'s attempt to build a global populist movement.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8804284}}\n\n{{Errol Morris}}\n\n[[Category:Steve Bannon]]\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:2018 documentary films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\